    "body": "Ha you're right, I did not add this to `package.json`.. \n\nIf adding `base64-js` to `node-browserify`'s dependencies is not an option then I could indeed split that into a new `browserify-buffer` package. \n\nHowever, buffers in native node code seem to be used a lot, so perhaps it would make sense to support them in `browserify`'s core..?\n\nAlso, `base64-js` is very small and prolly quite stable now so it could simply be added into `node-browserify`'s code..\n",
