    "created_at": "2012-05-24T22:58:35Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-05-24T22:58:35Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Extra module would be nice, indeed.. Besides, the correct name would be `buffer-browserify` – not `browserify-buffer` – to be able to resolve dependency automatically..\n\nHowever there is something special with the _buffer_ module in node. It is that this module is automatically present in the global namespace as the `Buffer` global variable. That's why most of (all ?) node modules depending on _buffer_ actually never use `require('buffer').Buffer`. These modules won't be compatible _ad-hoc_ with browserify if the _buffer_ module, and the `Buffer` global variable is not provided by default.\n\nSo the _ideal_ configuration would be for the _buffer_ module to be a built-in, loaded by default and added to the global namespace.. Unless other _ideal_ solutions exist ?..\n",
