    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Actually, `process` is already emulated by browserify by default and `console` doesn't need to be since it's already present in the browser.. I keep thinking that _buffer_ module is a really tricky and unique case - by the way I still wonder why, in node, it is not provided thru _require_ only, like other core modules.. (if anyone got the  answer ?). \n\nIt's even more tricky since _buffer_ is not a small module, so I understand that bundling it by default has a cost.. However I don't think that scanning the use of `Buffer` is an easy story, but in last resort..\n\nAnyway even if _buffer_ is provided as builtin, nothing prevents to delagate the maintain of _buffer_ module to an extra module (to be reusable..), declared as dependency in browserify, but with a kind of symbolic link to it (or [other way](https://github.com/substack/node-browserify/blob/master/builtins/sys.js)) in the _/builtins_ folder.\n",
