    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "`Buffer` is indeed a global variable in node, but it would also be quite heavy to include it in any `browserify` build... I haven't chimed a lot inside `node-browserify`'s internals, but could it be possible to define a top-level `Buffer` variable which implicitely adds the `buffer` module to the list of exported modules or fails if `buffer-browserify` is not available? Something like:\n\n```\nwindow.Buffer = function () {\n  // Tell browserify to export buffer\n  return require(\"buffer\").Buffer.apply(this, arguments);\n};\n```\n",
